author: SI Wire
title: Report: Mississippi State CB Will Redmond tears ACL
text:
Report: Mississippi State CB Will Redmond tears ACL Sports Illustrated 8 hrs ago SI Wire Â© Sports Illustrated will redmond torn acl mississippi state bulldogs
Mississippi State senior cornerback Will Redmond has a torn ACL and is likely to miss the remainder of the season, according to Michael Bonner of the Clarion-Ledger.
AdChoices Redmond reportedly sustained the injury in Wednesday's practice.
Redmond leads the Bulldogs defense with two interceptions and heads the cornerback corps with 25 tackles. Some analysts have pegged Redmond as a potential NFL first-round pick.
In his Mississippi State career, Redmond has collected 94 total tackles, 65 solo and 29 assisted, in 26 games.
Tolando Cleveland, who has started four games this season, could see an increase in playing time with Redmond's absence.
Mississippi State will take on Kentucky at home on Saturday.The Bulldogs and Wilcats are unranked in the latest Associated Press and Coaches Poll.
- Christopher Chavez
